<subSubSection id="1DEBB0596D7E6D162464E0FA69D3024C" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3CC8DD248E2CCC088861EDEBEF2F31DE" pageNumber="767">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName id="121153BF709826AB15438BFB3B395EA4" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182088" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole triplex Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole triplex Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplex">triplex</taxonomicName>
, three parts, referring to the tricolorous condition of the major.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FEBD74C4539A12DCFFDCD717E0ED3644" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CD1639233842BE55A8CD3D558C29E80A" pageNumber="767">
Diagnosis Major: virtually identical with 
<taxonomicName id="2BC93CBC35462FC254E13D9CE4710931" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata major</taxonomicName>
except for its much smaller size (HW about 0.8 mm versus more than 0.9 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="49BAE15EB3694284DA976737F5406453" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata</taxonomicName>
) and strikingly different color (see below). Stefan Cover, who has examined this species and 
<taxonomicName id="4B996B28DBEF4E101E019B4584D8C4FE" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata</taxonomicName>
in detail, reports that the head of the 
<taxonomicName id="943C374CC20CA9F573DDD111029B106B" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182088" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole triplex Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole triplex Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplex">triplex major</taxonomicName>
is also slightly narrower.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="18BE6E39105D7F8A44F7DE4EF5DD3C5A" type="description">
<paragraph id="3962D22943659A358AD10434164CF513" pageNumber="767">
Minor: virtually identical with 
<taxonomicName id="D83B8B10BA0D2765FE83428676C7038B" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata</taxonomicName>
minor except for its strikingly different color (see below). Another possible difference is habitat: the 
<taxonomicName id="A69310F32523972112F1B1766BCCC4A8" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182088" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole triplex Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole triplex Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplex">triplex</taxonomicName>
types were collected in mature mountain rainforest, while 
<taxonomicName id="E21B95A11EE90E4813356372165B42B3" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata</taxonomicName>
prefers open, even disturbed habitats. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.80, HL 1.06, SL 0.44, EL 0.12, PW 0.46. Paratype minor: HW 0.42, HL 0.46, SL 0.42, EL 0.09, PW 0.28.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FAE28ECEF3991B6BFE588FD1BC6BC1E3" pageNumber="767">Color Major: strongly tricolorous, with head and mandibles uniformly medium brown; mesosoma, waist, and appendages yellow;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB034197E3F89F50F945076A57D2D113" pageNumber="767">and gaster light brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C92670656AED1A19700B340704C42F9A" pageNumber="767">Minor: concolorous clear light yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1EBE8C374F10CE0D3F5E23C138C51947" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4B090A4D894E69097F556143EB2EC983" pageNumber="767">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DBD9BF3D4985258CC87899E61826468F" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="851B6065A22794730C0C52BE472EC5F5" pageNumber="767">Biology The type colony was found in mature montane rainforest, nesting beneath a rock in clay soil. A seed cache was present.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="602B8CC4A3E1805058A32D82FE2A3B0D" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="DBE3FE39F24B9B6923F07E5D49EBE0AE">Type locality TRINIDAD: Aripo Ridge, Arima Valley, 550-650 m (Stefan Cover and Mark W. Moffett). [Not figured]</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
